datacenter.tree
Class Level

java.lang.Object
  |
  +--datacenter.persistent.Persistent
        |
        +--datacenter.tree.Level
public class Level
extends Persistent

A Level is an abstract element of the tree hierarchy of the datacenter. A Level belongs to exactly one parent, except for the root that has no parent. Thus a given Level may have zero, one or more child Levels. NOTE: objects of this class can only be read from the database, it is not possible to create new database objects of this type.

See Also:
Container, Persistent
